The expression $24x^2-19x-35$ can be factored as $(3x-5)(8x+7)$. Therefore, $(Ax-5)=(3x-5)$ and $(2Bx+C)=(8x+7)$. From that, $A=3$, $B=4$, and $C=7$. \begin{align*}
AB-3C&=3\cdot4-3\cdot7\\
&=12-21\\
